WEBVTT

00:10.540 --> 00:11.540
CHAPTER III.

00:11.920 --> 00:14.100
IS OPPORTUNITY MONOPOLISED?

00:15.040 --> 00:19.700
No man is kept poor because opportunity has been taken away from him, because other people

00:19.700 --> 00:22.880
have monopolised the wealth and have put a fence around it.

00:23.100 --> 00:27.580
You may be shut off from engaging in business in certain lines, but there are other channels

00:27.580 --> 00:28.480
open to you.

00:28.480 --> 00:32.920
Probably it would be hard for you to get control of any of the great rail-load systems.

00:33.320 --> 00:35.180
That field is pretty well monopolised.

00:35.680 --> 00:40.280
But the electric railway business is still in its infancy, and offers plenty of scope

00:40.280 --> 00:41.180
for enterprise.

00:41.780 --> 00:46.280
And it will be with a few years, until traffic and transportation through the air will become

00:46.280 --> 00:50.860
a great industry, and in all its branches will give employment to hundreds of thousands

00:50.860 --> 00:52.620
and perhaps to millions of people.

00:53.080 --> 00:58.120
Why not turn your attention to the development of aerial transportation, instead of competing

00:58.120 --> 01:01.880
with J.J. Hill and others for a chance in the steam railway world?

01:02.680 --> 01:06.980
It is quite true that if you are a workman in the employ of the steel-trust, you have

01:06.980 --> 01:10.160
very little chance of becoming the owner of the plant in which you work.

01:10.460 --> 01:15.220
But it is also true that if you will commence the act in a certain way, you can soon leave

01:15.220 --> 01:16.720
the employ of the steel-trust.

01:16.980 --> 01:22.840
You can buy a farm of from 10 to 40 acres, and engage in business as a producer of foodstuffs.

01:23.300 --> 01:28.020
There is great opportunity at this time for men, who will live upon small tracts of land

01:28.020 --> 01:30.140
and cultivate the same intensively.

01:30.520 --> 01:32.280
Such men will certainly get rich.

01:32.740 --> 01:36.800
You may say that it is impossible for you to get the land, but I am going to prove to

01:36.800 --> 01:41.260
you that it is not impossible, and that you can certainly get a farm if you will go to

01:41.260 --> 01:42.420
work in a certain way.

01:42.960 --> 01:48.000
At different periods, the tide of opportunity sets in different directions, according to

01:48.000 --> 01:52.700
needs of the whole, and the particular state of social evolution which has been reached.

01:53.180 --> 01:58.420
At present, in America, it is setting toward agriculture and the allied industries and

01:58.420 --> 01:59.040
professions.

01:59.660 --> 02:03.280
Today, opportunity is open before the factory worker in his line.

02:03.620 --> 02:08.280
It is open before the businessman, who supplies the farmer more than before the one who supplies

02:08.280 --> 02:13.300
the factory worker, and before the professional man, who waits upon the farmer more than before

02:13.300 --> 02:15.120
the one who serves the working class.

02:15.120 --> 02:19.860
There is abundance of opportunity for the man who will go with the tide, instead of

02:19.860 --> 02:21.340
trying to swim against it.

02:21.820 --> 02:27.280
So the factory workers, either as individuals or as a class, are not deprived of opportunity.

02:27.740 --> 02:30.380
The workers are not being kept down by their masters.

02:30.860 --> 02:34.200
They are not being ground by the trusts and combinations of capital.

02:34.720 --> 02:38.960
As a class, they are where they are because they do not do things in a certain way.

02:39.440 --> 02:44.220
If the workers of America chose to do so, they could follow the example of their brothers

02:44.220 --> 02:49.500
in Belgium and other countries, and establish great department stores and cooperative industries.

02:50.120 --> 02:54.880
They could elect men of their own class to office, and pass laws favoring the development

02:54.880 --> 03:00.020
of such cooperative industries, and in a few years they could take peaceable possession

03:00.020 --> 03:01.500
of the industrial field.

03:02.580 --> 03:07.020
The working class may become the master class whenever they will begin to do things in a

03:07.020 --> 03:07.640
certain way.

03:07.820 --> 03:11.220
The law of wealth is the same for them as it is for all others.

03:11.700 --> 03:16.660
This they must learn, and they will remain where they are, as long as they continue to

03:16.660 --> 03:17.520
do as they do.

03:17.880 --> 03:23.540
The individual worker, however, is not held down by the ignorance or the mental slothfulness

03:23.540 --> 03:24.400
of his class.

03:24.900 --> 03:29.480
He can follow the tide of opportunity to riches, and this book will tell them how.

03:30.240 --> 03:33.680
No one is kept in poverty by a shortness in the supply of riches.

03:34.060 --> 03:35.580
There is more than enough for all.

03:35.880 --> 03:40.580
A palace as large as the capital at Washington might be built for every family on earth,

03:40.580 --> 03:45.920
from the building material in the United States alone, and under intensive cultivation this

03:45.920 --> 03:50.980
country would produce wool, cotton, linen, and silk enough to cloth each person in the

03:50.980 --> 03:55.540
world finer than Solomon was arrayed in all his glory, together with food enough to feed

03:55.540 --> 03:56.920
them all luxuriously.

03:57.480 --> 04:03.420
The visible supply is practically inexhaustible, and the invisible supply really is inexhaustible.

04:04.040 --> 04:08.600
Everything you see on earth is made from one original substance, out of which all things

04:08.600 --> 04:09.120
proceed.

04:10.100 --> 04:16.300
New forms are constantly being made, and older ones are dissolving, but all are shapes assumed

04:16.300 --> 04:17.280
by one thing.

04:18.240 --> 04:22.520
There is no limit to the supply of formless stuff or original substance.

04:23.220 --> 04:27.380
The universe is made out of it, but it is not all used in making the universe.

04:27.900 --> 04:32.800
The spaces in, through, and between the forms of the visible universe are permeated and

04:32.800 --> 04:37.300
filled with the original substance, with the formless stuff, with the raw material of all

04:37.300 --> 04:37.720
things.

04:38.280 --> 04:43.200
Ten thousand times as much as has been made might still be made, and even then we should

04:43.200 --> 04:46.220
not have exhausted the supply of universal raw material.

04:46.920 --> 04:51.400
No man, therefore, is poor because nature is poor, or because there is not enough to

04:51.400 --> 04:52.020
go around.

04:52.740 --> 04:55.360
Nature is an inexhaustible storehouse of riches.

04:55.820 --> 04:57.720
The supply will never run short.

04:58.320 --> 05:03.500
Original substance is alive with creative energy, and is constantly producing more forms.

05:04.100 --> 05:07.960
When the supply of building material is exhausted, more will be produced.

05:08.300 --> 05:13.100
When the soil is exhausted, so that foodstuffs and materials for clothing will no longer

05:13.100 --> 05:16.860
grow upon it, it will be renewed, or more soil will be made.

05:17.420 --> 05:21.820
When all the gold and silver has been dug from the earth, if man is still in such a

05:21.820 --> 05:26.160
stage of social development that he needs gold and silver, more will be produced from

05:26.160 --> 05:26.880
the formless.

05:27.300 --> 05:29.940
The formless stuff responds to the needs of man.

05:29.940 --> 05:32.580
It will not let him be without any good thing.

05:33.620 --> 05:35.360
This is true of man collectively.

05:35.920 --> 05:40.960
The race as a whole is always abundantly rich, and if individuals are poor, it is because

05:40.960 --> 05:45.760
they do not follow the certain way of doing things, which makes the individual man rich.

05:46.440 --> 05:48.140
The formless stuff is intelligent.

05:48.620 --> 05:50.160
It is stuff which thinks.

05:50.660 --> 05:53.780
It is alive, and is always impelled toward more life.

05:54.380 --> 05:58.120
It is the natural and inherent impulse of life to seek to live more.

05:58.120 --> 06:03.280
It is the nature of intelligence to enlarge itself, and of consciousness to seek to extend

06:03.280 --> 06:05.680
its boundaries and find fuller expression.

06:06.740 --> 06:11.940
The universe of forms has been made by formless living substance, throwing itself into form

06:11.940 --> 06:14.200
in order to express itself more fully.

06:14.980 --> 06:20.220
The universe is a great living presence, always moving inherently toward more life and fuller

06:20.220 --> 06:20.680
functioning.

06:21.500 --> 06:24.020
Nature is formed for the advancement of life.

06:24.520 --> 06:26.980
Its impelling motive is the increase of life.

06:27.400 --> 06:32.160
For this cause, everything which can possibly minister to life is bountifully provided.

06:32.580 --> 06:37.120
There can be no lack unless God is to contradict Himself and nullify His own works.

06:37.660 --> 06:40.720
You are not kept poor by lacking the supply of riches.

06:41.180 --> 06:46.140
It is a fact that I shall demonstrate a little farther on, that even the resources of the

06:46.140 --> 06:50.740
formless supply are at the command of the man or woman, who will act and think in a

06:50.740 --> 06:51.500
certain way.

